{"title":"ITU Persona Mayor iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/ITU Persona Mayor iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Infección del Tracto Urinario\\Nen Persona Mayor","guid":"XFbPKH3Wmsbi8iBrR4Jt8g","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"ITU = infección bacteriana MÁS FRECUENTE en >65 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"404.61 millones de casos globales/año (2021)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Prevalencia bacteriuria asintomática → 25-50% mujeres institucionalizadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Prevalencia bacteriuria asintomática → 15-40% hombres institucionalizados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"2.8 millones hospitalizaciones con dx ITU en EEUU (2018)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Mortalidad asociada → 236,790 muertes globales/año","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"Agente PRINCIPAL → Escherichia coli (64-80%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"Otros → Klebsiella pneumoniae, Proteus mirabilis, Enterococcus spp","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"Proteus spp → asociado a catéter y litiasis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"0","text":"Factores de Riesgo\\Nen Persona Mayor","guid":"Q5zediycb83El-3Ra2lIFQ","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Mujer → atrofia urogenital, prolapso, incontinencia, residuo postmiccional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"Hombre → hiperplasia prostática, obstrucción, cateterización","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"Comunes ambos sexos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"Catéter urinario permanente → PRINCIPAL factor modificable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"Diabetes mellitus → glucosuria favorece colonización","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"14","text":"Deterioro cognitivo → higiene comprometida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"14","text":"Inmovilidad → vaciamiento vesical incompleto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"14","text":"Incontinencia urinaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"14","text":"Institucionalización (ELEAM/LTCF)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"14","text":"Inmunosenescencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"14","text":"Uso previo de antibióticos → selección de resistencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"14","text":"Urolitiasis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"14","text":"Vejiga neurogénica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación IDSA 2025","guid":"","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"ITU NO COMPLICADA → infección confinada a vejiga","guid":"","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"Aplica a MUJERES Y HOMBRES (novedad 2025)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"Hombre afebril sin signos sistémicos → puede ser no complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"Síntomas → disuria, urgencia, frecuencia, dolor suprapúbico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"25","text":"ITU COMPLICADA → infección más allá de vejiga","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Fiebre, escalofríos, dolor en flanco, sensibilidad ángulo costovertebral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"Dispositivos urinarios (catéter, stent, nefrostomía)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"Obstrucción o retención urinaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"Incluye pielonefritis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"30","text":"Incluye ITU asociada a catéter (CAUTI)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"30","text":"Incluye ITU bacterémica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"25","text":"CAMBIO PARADIGMA → ya no se clasifica por factores de riesgo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Edad >65 NO define automáticamente como complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"Sexo masculino NO define automáticamente como complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"Diabetes NO define automáticamente como complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"Se basa en SIGNOS CLÍNICOS OBSERVABLES","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"0","text":"Bacteriuria Asintomática (BA) — TRAMPA GERIÁTRICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Definición → >=10^5 UFC/mL SIN síntomas urinarios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"Prevalencia ALTA en AM → NO requiere tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"IDSA 2019 → NO tratar BA en personas mayores (Recomendación FUERTE)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"42","text":"NO tratar BA post-caída sin fiebre ni signos sistémicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"42","text":"NO tratar BA en deterioro cognitivo sin signos focales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"42","text":"NO tratar BA en pacientes con catéter crónico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"42","text":"EXCEPCIONES para tratar BA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"Previo a cirugía urológica con sangrado mucoso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"Embarazo (no aplica en geriatría habitualmente)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"42","text":"Tratamiento de BA → selecciona resistencia, causa RAM, NO mejora outcomes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"42","text":"Urocultivo → NO solicitar de rutina sin síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"42","text":"Piuria aislada → NO indica infección en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico en Persona Mayor — DESAFÍOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Síntomas clásicos pueden estar AUSENTES","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Disuria puede no reportarse (deterioro cognitivo, afasia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Frecuencia/urgencia → confundido con incontinencia basal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"55","text":"Síntomas INESPECÍFICOS → NO atribuir automáticamente a ITU","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Confusión/delirium → buscar OTRAS causas primero","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"Caídas → NO es criterio para iniciar ATB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"Deterioro funcional → evaluación multidimensional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"59","text":"Inapetencia, astenia → son inespecíficos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"55","text":"Criterios mínimos para iniciar ATB (Loeb/McGeer modificados)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Disuria aguda (<1 semana)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"O fiebre (>37.9C o >1.5C sobre basal) + 1 síntoma urinario nuevo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"Síntomas urinarios nuevos → urgencia, frecuencia, hematuria macroscópica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"Dolor suprapúbico nuevo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"64","text":"Dolor en flanco/ángulo costovertebral","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"55","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Orina completa → leucocituria, nitritos, esterasa leucocitaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"Urocultivo → SIEMPRE antes de ATB empírico si es posible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"70","text":"Hemocultivos → en ITU febril/complicada","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"32.4% bacteriemia en AM hospitalizados con ITU febril","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"Discordancia hemocultivo-urocultivo FRECUENTE en AM","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"70","text":"Procalcitonina → puede orientar infección sistémica vs BA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"70","text":"PCR → útil en seguimiento, no diagnóstica aislada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"55","text":"Imágenes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"No rutinarias en ITU no complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"Eco renal/vesical → sospecha obstrucción, retención","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"78","text":"TAC → absceso, pionefrosis, litiasis obstructiva","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento Empírico —\\NPOR PERFIL DE PACIENTE","guid":"Yg0qzNDStO0aMlHKCEHKCA","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"ITU NO COMPLICADA AMBULATORIA (cistitis)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"PRIMERA LÍNEA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"Nitrofurantoína 100mg c/12h x 5 días","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"Requiere VFG >30 mL/min → VERIFICAR en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"NO útil si sospecha pielonefritis (mala penetración tisular)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"85","text":"RAM → náuseas, toxicidad pulmonar crónica (uso prolongado)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"84","text":"Fosfomicina 3g dosis única VO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Buena opción en E. coli productora BLEE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"NO usar en ITU complicada (IDSA 2025)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Menor eficacia vs cursos de 5 días","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"84","text":"TMP-SMX 160/800mg c/12h x 3 días (si resistencia local <20%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Verificar antibiograma local","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"RAM → hiperpotasemia en AM, rash, discrasias","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"83","text":"SEGUNDA LÍNEA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Amoxicilina-clavulánico 875/125mg c/12h x 5-7 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"Cefalosporinas orales (cefadroxilo, cefalexina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"Fluoroquinolonas → RESERVAR para cuando no hay alternativa","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"Ciprofloxacino 500mg c/12h x 3 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"Riesgo en AM → tendinopatía, QTc, delirium, C. difficile","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"EVITAR como primera línea (stewardship)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"82","text":"ITU COMPLICADA AMBULATORIA\\N(pielonefritis, febril)","guid":"0lpJXmd4QlaX2ATu3Tc3gg","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"PRIMERA LÍNEA ORAL (IDSA 2025)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Fluoroquinolona (ciprofloxacino 500mg c/12h, levofloxacino 750mg/día)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Duración → 5-7 días","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"TMP-SMX 160/800mg c/12h x 7 días (si susceptible)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"Amoxicilina-clavulánico x 7 días (si susceptible)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"103","text":"Considerar dosis IM inicial de ceftriaxona 1g si hay duda sobre absorción oral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"103","text":"NO usar nitrofurantoína ni fosfomicina en ITU complicada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"82","text":"ITU COMPLICADA HOSPITALIZADA (sepsis, inestabilidad)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Paso 1 → evaluar gravedad (sepsis vs no sepsis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Paso 2 → evaluar riesgo de resistencia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"ATB previos en 90 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"Hospitalización reciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"Institucionalización","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"Catéter urinario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"Antibiograma local","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"111","text":"Paso 3 → seleccionar esquema empírico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"SIN factores de riesgo MDR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"Ceftriaxona 2g/día IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"Cefotaxima 2g c/8h IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"120","text":"Ertapenem 1g/día IV (si sospecha BLEE local alta)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"119","text":"CON factores de riesgo MDR o SEPSIS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"Piperacilina-tazobactam 4.5g c/6h IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"Cefepime 2g c/8h IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Meropenem 1g c/8h IV (si sospecha BLEE/AmpC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"124","text":"Considerar aminoglucósido como puente (amikacina 15mg/kg)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"119","text":"Enterococo sospechado (Gram+ en orina)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Ampicilina 2g c/6h IV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Vancomicina si E. faecium o alergia","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"111","text":"Paso 4 → desescalar según urocultivo a las 48-72h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"111","text":"Switch IV a VO → cuando mejoría clínica + tolera VO + ATB oral efectivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"111","text":"Duración total → 7 días (fluoroquinolona 5-7 días)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"111","text":"Bacteriemia Gram negativa documentada → 7 días totales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"82","text":"ITU ASOCIADA A CATÉTER (CAUTI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Primer paso → CAMBIAR O RETIRAR CATÉTER","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"136","text":"Si catéter >2 semanas → cambiar antes de tomar urocultivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"136","text":"Tratamiento → igual que ITU complicada según perfil","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"136","text":"Duración → 7 días (si respuesta rápida), 10-14 días (si respuesta lenta)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"136","text":"NO tratar bacteriuria de catéter sin síntomas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"82","text":"AM EN INSTITUCIONES (ELEAM/LTCF)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"143","parent":"142","text":"Antibiograma institucional → FUNDAMENTAL para elección empírica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"142","text":"Criterios Loeb → mínimo para iniciar ATB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"142","text":"Preferir esquemas orales si estabilidad clínica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"142","text":"Nitrofurantoína → buena opción si VFG adecuada y cistitis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"142","text":"Derivar si → sepsis, obstrucción, falla de tratamiento oral","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones Geriátricas Específicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"Función renal → SIEMPRE ajustar por VFGe (CKD-EPI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Nitrofurantoína CI si VFG <30","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"Aminoglucósidos → monitorizar niveles, nefrotoxicidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"TMP-SMX → riesgo hiperpotasemia con IECA/ARA2/espironolactona","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"149","text":"Fluoroquinolonas → ajustar por VFG si <30","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"148","text":"Interacciones farmacológicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Warfarina + TMP-SMX → aumento INR significativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"154","text":"Warfarina + fluoroquinolonas → aumento INR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"154","text":"Metformina + TMP → riesgo hipoglicemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"154","text":"Digoxina + amoxicilina → aumento niveles digoxina","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"148","text":"Riesgo de C. difficile → ALTO en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"Fluoroquinolonas, cefalosporinas 3ra gen, clindamicina → mayor riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"Nitrofurantoína → MENOR riesgo de C. difficile","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"Fosfomicina → menor impacto en microbioma","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"148","text":"Delirium secundario a ITU","guid":"","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"ITU como precipitante → solo si ITU verdadera (no BA)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"Delirium por ATB → fluoroquinolonas pueden causar neurotoxicidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"Evaluar CAM/4AT antes y durante tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"167","parent":"148","text":"Polifarmacia → revisar STOPP/START al prescribir ATB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"148","text":"Cascada de prescripción → ATB → diarrea → loperamida → estreñimiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"148","text":"Fragilidad → considerar vía de administración, tolerancia oral, hidratación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"0","text":"Prevención","guid":"","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"NO FARMACOLÓGICA → PRIMERA LÍNEA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"Hidratación adecuada (1.5L/día si no hay restricción)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"171","text":"Higiene perineal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"171","text":"Retiro precoz de catéter → CADA DÍA evaluar necesidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"171","text":"Estrógenos vaginales tópicos en mujeres postmenopáusicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"Reducen ITU recurrente (NNT ~5-8)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"No contraindicados en ca mama con oncología aprobando","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"178","parent":"171","text":"Movilización → evitar inmovilidad prolongada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"171","text":"Manejo incontinencia → programas de vaciamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"170","text":"FARMACOLÓGICA (ITU recurrente >=3/año)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"Profilaxis ATB → último recurso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Nitrofurantoína 50-100mg nocturna","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"TMP-SMX 40/200mg nocturna","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"180","text":"D-Manosa → evidencia limitada pero bajo riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"180","text":"Arándano (cranberry) → evidencia INCONSISTENTE en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"180","text":"Metenamina hipurato → alternativa no ATB prometedora","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"180","text":"Vacunas (OM-89/Uro-Vaxom) → estimulación inmune, evidencia moderada","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"Bacteriuria asintomática NO es ITU → NO tratar en AM (IDSA 2019, recomendación fuerte)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"188","text":"Urocultivo turbio o maloliente → NO indica ITU sin síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"188","text":"Delirium + bacteriuria NO = ITU → buscar OTRAS causas primero","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"188","text":"Caída + urocultivo positivo NO = ITU → no iniciar ATB sin criterios Loeb","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"188","text":"Nitrofurantoína → verificar VFG >30, toxicidad pulmonar si uso >6 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"188","text":"Estrógenos vaginales → infrautilizados en prevención ITU recurrente en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"188","text":"IDSA 2025 → hombre afebril con cistitis puede tratarse como no complicada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"188","text":"Siempre obtener urocultivo ANTES de ATB empírico en AM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"188","text":"Cambiar catéter antes de tomar muestra si lleva >2 semanas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"188","text":"Switch IV a VO cuando mejora clínica + tolera oral + ATB oral efectivo disponible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"188","text":"Antibiograma LOCAL define la elección empírica → no seguir guías ciegas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"200","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"1. Nicolle LE et al. Clinical Practice Guideline for the Management of Asymptomatic Bacteriuria: 2019 Update by IDSA. Clin Infect Dis. 2019;68(10):e83-e110.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"200","text":"2. Trautner BW et al. IDSA Clinical Practice Guideline for the Treatment of Complicated UTI. Clin Infect Dis. 2025.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"200","text":"3. Gupta K et al. International Clinical Practice Guidelines for the Treatment of Acute Uncomplicated Cystitis and Pyelonephritis in Women: A 2010 Update by IDSA/ESCMID. Clin Infect Dis. 2011;52(5):e103-e120.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"200","text":"4. Álvarez Artero E et al. Utility of blood culture in febrile UTI in the elderly. Rev Esp Quimioter. 2021;34(3):249-253.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"200","text":"5. Loeb M et al. Development of minimum criteria for the initiation of antibiotics in residents of long-term-care facilities. Infect Control Hosp Epidemiol. 2001;22(2):120-124.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"200","text":"6. AUA/CUA/SUFU Guideline. Recurrent Uncomplicated UTI in Women. 2025 Update.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"200","text":"7. Koh SWC et al. Antibiotic treatment failure of uncomplicated UTI in primary care. Antimicrob Resist Infect Control. 2023;12(1):73.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"200","text":"8. Bista B, Champion JD. UTI treatment and antibiotic stewardship program guidelines. J Am Assoc Nurse Pract. 2019;31(12):693-698.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":208,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"ITU Persona Mayor iPad","id":"map_780","resolved_references":[]}